Caroline Bruzelius: I think it’s going to take quite a while to really understand the extent of the damage and to which parts.
That fire was immense and incredibly hot—although stone won’t actually burn, it can be terribly damaged by great heat.
I am imagining, though I don’t know, that this restoration will take at least a decade.
FP: And I guess it will be a long, long time before the public can gain access again.
But you know one thing I’m hoping is that the public will become more aware of the fragility of our historical buildings.